2. Checks and Validations

2.1. Effect size - Benchmark calculation

library(psych)

# Data from: Macchi, G., De Pisapia, N. Virtual reality, face-to-face, and 2D video conferencing differently impact fatigue, creativity, flow, and decision-making in workplace dynamics. Sci Rep 14, 10260 (2024). https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-024-60942-6

# Function calculating Cohen's d

cohen_d <- function (mean1, sd1,mean2, sd2,n1,n2) 
{
  sd_pooled <- sqrt(((n1 - 1) * sd1^2 + (n2 - 1) * sd2^2) / (n1 + n2 - 2))

cohens_d <- (mean1 - mean2) / sd_pooled
  
  return(cohens_d)
}

# Perceived outcome importance 

cohen_d(2.38,0.88,3.12,1.14,40,40)

# Absorption by activity

cohen_d(4.55,0.88,5.05,0.95,40,40)

# Social emotional area: positive reactions

cohen_d(76.90 ,16.18, 97.40, 22.55,40,40)

# Task area: attempted answers

cohen_d(82.10, 12.82, 101.3, 15.55,40,40)

# Task area: questions

cohen_d(15.00, 8.58, 24.00, 10.02,40,40)

4. Main Analysis

4.1. H1: Effect on Group dynamics

 library(lmtest)
library(car)

# R1 - Simple Linear Regression

model_1 <- lm(group_dyn ~ treat, data = final_data)
summary(model_1)

# Assumptions checks function

ass_check <- function(model)
  
{  #Linearity
  
  p1 <- plot(model, 1)

  # Independence of Errors
  
t1<-dwtest(model)

  # Homoscedasticity

t2<-bptest(model)

  # Normality of errors 

p2<-plot(model, 2)

# Test for Influential outliers

p3<-plot(model,which=4)
  
result <- list(
    plot1 = p1,
    test1 = t1,
    test2 = t2,
    plot2 = p2,
    plot3 = p3)

return(result) 
}

ass_check(model_1)
# R2 - Multiple linear regression, selected covariates (see appendix for reasoning)

model_2 <- lm(group_dyn ~ treat + group_size + ppl_known_in_group_num  + tired_end + baseline_relies_on_others + baseline_trusts_others+
baseline_believes_in_good_int +
  tech_issues + prior_VR_experience_num   + best_ind_score_in_g +ind_task_score +
   group_perf +
enjoyable_group_task + present_group_task  +  group_task_time_min,  
  data = final_data)
summary(model_2)

# Assumptions checks

ass_check(model_2)
# Function creating a table with VIF outputs to check for Multicollinearity

vif_function <- function(model) {
  vif_df <- data.frame(
  Predictor = names(vif(model)),
  VIF = round(as.numeric(vif(model)),2))

  return(vif_df)}

vif_function(model_2)


# R3 - Multiple linear regression, selected covariates, highly non-significant predictors removed

model_3 <- lm(group_dyn ~ treat  + tired_end + baseline_relies_on_others + baseline_trusts_others+
  tech_issues  +ind_task_score +
enjoyable_group_task + present_group_task  +  group_task_time_min,  
  data = final_data)
summary(model_3)


ass_check(model_3)
vif_function(model_3)


# Function for Reporting Regression results

stat_table <- function(model){
  
  coef_summary <- summary(model)$coefficients
  confint <- confint(model, level = 0.95)
  
  results_df <- data.frame(
#  Predictor = rownames(coef_summary),
  Estimate = round(coef_summary[, "Estimate"],3),
  StdError = round(coef_summary[, "Std. Error"],3),
   CI1 = round(confint[, 1],3),
  CI2 = round(confint[, 2],3),
  tValue = round(coef_summary[, "t value"],3),
  pValue = round(coef_summary[, "Pr(>|t|)"],3)
 
  )
  
  return(results_df)
}


# Regression results tables - R1-R3

stat_table(model_1)
stat_table(model_2)
stat_table(model_3)

# Creating a function that compares Duration in muntes of time spent of different activities across the two conditions

box_plot_conditions <- function(var, col_1, col_2, title) {
  
 VR_df_var <- VR_data[, var]

colnames(VR_df_var) <- c("VR")

VC_df_var <- VC_data[, var]

colnames(VC_df_var) <- c("VC")

VR_df_var  <- gather(VR_df_var , key = "condition", value = "duration_min")

VC_df_var  <- gather(VC_df_var , key = "condition", value = "duration_min")

All_df_var <- bind_rows(VR_df_var, VC_df_var)
  
 plot <- ggplot(All_df_var, aes(x = condition, y = duration_min, fill = condition)) +
 geom_boxplot() +  
  ylim(0, 24) +
  labs(title = title, x = "Condition", y = "Duration (mins)")  + scale_fill_manual(values = c( col_2,col_1)) +
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 15), 
          axis.title.x = element_text(size = 12), 
    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 12), 
    axis.text = element_text(size = 15))

  return(plot)
}
